Stream receive-pack sideband muxers through a spawned helper on WASI.

receive-pack uses the same in-process async facility for hook stderr,
connectivity progress, and index-pack progress. On WASI, async startup falls
back to unavailable fork(); most callers then lose progress and the unpack
path incorrectly returns success without consuming the pack.

Reuse the hidden sideband multicall helper as a streaming mux process. The
helper reads bounded 128-byte chunks exactly like upstream copy_to_sideband(),
including keepalives, while its stdin pipe provides backpressure. Native builds
retain the existing async implementation. Treat mux startup or exit failure as
an unpack failure instead of silently skipping the pack.

